2026-07-22T23:09:12.9416346Z             "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds optional external identity provider (IdP) authentication alongside the existing token-based auth. Users can now authenticate via interactive OpenID Connect single sign-on (SSO), and service accounts can use IdP-issued JWT bearer tokens. Both methods run side-by-side with token auth and can be independently enabled/disabled.\n\n## Key Changes\n\n**Authentication & Authorization**\n- New `OidcSettings` and `JwtBearerSettings` classes for startup-time configuration of external IdP methods\n- `ExternalUserMapper` service maps external principals (OIDC/JWT claims) to the existing `AuthService.User` shape\n- ASP.NET Core authentication handlers registered for:\n  - Cookie-based SSO sessions (`EdnsvSession` scheme)\n  - Interactive OIDC challenge/callback flow (`Oidc` scheme)\n  - JWT bearer token validation (`EntraBearer` scheme)\n- Data Protection key ring persisted to `{dataDir}/keys` so SSO sessions survive restarts\n- Gate middleware and startup validation updated to recognize `anyAuthEnabled` (token OR OIDC OR JWT) vs. `externalAuthEnabled` (OIDC OR JWT)\n\n**Config & Audit**\n- `ConfigService` now tracks revision history with user attribution and timestamps\n- `ConfigRevision` and `ConfigRevisionInfo` types added for history endpoints\n- New `/api/config/history` and `/api/config/history/{id}` endpoints (admin-only)\n- Elevated revoke for external-IdP admins (can revoke unrelated users, not just descendants)\n- Audit logging captures SSO sign-ins, config changes, and token operations with optional trace masking\n\n**UI & Documentation**\n- Login page updated with SSO button and divider when OIDC is enabled\n- Config page enhanced with select dropdowns for role/claim configuration\n- New `entra-setup.md` guide for Entra ID (Azure AD) integration\n- Updated `configuration.md` with all new `Auth:Oidc:*` and `Auth:JwtBearer:*` settings\n\n**Testing**\n- New `Ednsv.Web.Tests` project with comprehensive test coverage:\n  - `TokenAuthTests` — regression baseline for token auth\n  - `OidcFlowTests` — SSO flow up to IdP redirect\n  - `JwtBearerAuthTests` — service-account JWT validation\n  - `AuthModeMatrixTests` — auth method combinations and gate behavior\n  - `AuditLoggingTests` — security-sensitive operation logging\n  - `ConfigHistoryAndRevokeTests` — revision history and elevated revoke\n- `EdnsvAppFactory` test helper boots the real app with in-memory IdP metadata and forged session/JWT tokens\n- `ListLoggerProvider` captures logs for assertion in tests\n- `ExternalUserMapperTests` and `ConfigServiceTests` added to core tests\n\n## Notable Implementation Details\n\n- **No IdP network calls in tests**: External IdP metadata is replaced with static in-memory configuration and a test RSA key\n- **Session cookie security**: `SameSite=Lax` (not Strict) to allow cross-site sign-in redirect while preserving CSRF protection on state-changing endpoints\n- **Deterministic trace masking**: Hash function allows masked values to correlate across log lines for a given salt\n- **Fail-closed startup**: Invalid external auth config (missing required fields, validation errors) prevents the app from starting\n- **Backward compatible**: Token auth remains the default; external IdP methods are opt-in via configuration\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01PRd7GEH8at5RYwqsD6AdGN",
